simple_shell

NAME
	simple_shell || ./hsh

SYNOPSIS

	"main.h"
	$ [commands]..[flags] || $ [echo]..[commands]..[flag] | [./hsh]

DESCRIPTION

	Bash is an sh-compatible command language interpreter that executes
	commands read from the standard input or from a file.

LIBRARIES

	#include <sys/stat.h>
	#include <stdio.h>
	#include <stdlib.h>
	#include <unistd.h>
	#include <stdarg.h>
	#include <string.h>
	#include <signal.h>
	#include <sys/wait.h>

INTERACTIVE AND NON-INTERACTIVE MODE

	This Shell must work in both modes:

	Interactive mode:

	($) ./hsh
	($) /bin/ls
	hsh main.c shell.c
	($)
	($) exit
	($)

	Non interactive mode:

	($) echo "bin/ls" | ./hsh
	hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
	($)
	($) cat test_ls_2
	/bin/ls
	/bin/ls
	($)
	($) cat test_ls_2 | ./hsh
	hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
	hsh main.c shell.c test_ls_2
	($)

COMPILATION

	This shell will be compiled this way:

	gcc -Wall -Werror -Wextra -pedantic -std=gnu89 *.c -o hsh

STYLE

	This code uses the Betty style code

SIGNALS

	CTRL D - close the interface session

	CTRL C - kill a process that is running at the moment

BUILT-IN

	exit - causes the immediate kill of the process corresponding to the shell
		that is reading the script.

	env - prints the current environment.

OUTPUT

	The Output that this command interpreter throws is the same one that the CMD
	throws when entering a command to the execution line in case it is correct,
	otherwise, it will throw the corresponding error based on the command passed
	by the user.

AUTHORS

	MATEO ARBINI
	VALENTIN REPETTO
